text:
Not a place where everyone could go at anytime and feel at home anymore!
It's feels like a workspace, library and no space for individuals and family to chill..
It's a student lounge for students to do thier group assignments and workpeople to hog the entire space for all day long.
I am very disappointed with the experience.  Hope the management could put a time limit like Starbucks or stop students from using the space and be mindful for others too. Be gracious  society not a selfish one. Thank youüôèüèΩ

Good vibes, pleasant place to hang out. Stop here regularly when I am not put off by the price (and small double double is still 1.70 back home). Go to sandwich is pesto chicken, though this time it seemed a bit light on the chicken.

Highly recommend the double double (with skim mill for the weight conscious, traditionally this is served with cream).

The coffee won't impress the connossoirs, but it's the taste I grew up with and nice to see they haven't tried to 'elevate it'.

Ordered maple cinnamon latte and donut. Drink is nice but donut not worth for the money. Again tried their latte today the taste remains same. Also tried the Triple Cheese Toast was so TASTY. Only little expensive üòÅ
Chance upon this cafe while walking around Jurong Point. The staff is very friendly. A nice and comfortable place to have a bite of Donut and a cup of warm coffee.

Back on 12 April 2024 at Jurong Point was opening called Tim Hortons Singapore many customers were visit at this outlet.

Today I‚Äôve signed up on Tim Hortons Singapore App rather can redeem Free Daily Brew Coffee $4.70 for 100% complimentary. Also buy Maple Salted Caramel Donut & Medium Salted Caramel Macchiato Iced Cappuccino.

Thank you Tim Hortons Singapore for appreciate that. Will try to visit next time!!
